# County AI Assurance Operations Center Rules

Before making changes, read `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `CODEX.md`, and `docs/ai-context/current-state.md`.

Preserve the project philosophy:

- Operational simplicity.
- Governance-first design.
- Findings and evidence first.
- One or two operators.
- Single Linux VM.
- Docker Compose first.
- Mock-first development.

Do not add Kubernetes, microservices, distributed workers, enterprise auth, multi-tenant SaaS assumptions, or real scanner integrations unless explicitly requested.

Scanner integrations must use adapters. The platform orchestrates scanners, normalizes results, preserves evidence, creates findings, and scores risk. It does not rewrite scanner tools.

The UI should feel authoritative, calm, security-focused, audit-friendly, and government-grade. Avoid neon AI styling, chatbot-first layouts, toy dashboards, and vague AI magic language.

When implementation status changes, update `docs/ai-context/implementation-status.md` and the relevant todo file.
